<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Air Force Attacks PKK Camp in Northern Iraq 18 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Air Force Attacks PKK Camp in Northern Iraq 18 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1805103894 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1805103894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over still of regional map] </F>
  [Text] The Turkish Air Force today launched an air raid on 
the Zhala camp in northern Iraq belonging to the PKK [Workers 
Party of Kurdistan]. It is reported that all targets were 
completely destroyed in the operation. The Chief of Staff's 
Press and Public Relations Office issued the following statement 
on the issue: 
  Intelligence information has been received that the bandits 
are regrouping in the Zhala camp in northern Iraq, which was 
rendered ineffective as a result of an air raid launched by the 
Turkish Air Force on 28 January 1994, and that they are 
preparing to engage in various activities. Between 1200 and 1230 
today, the Turkish Armed Forces used 19 planes, eight of which 
have air to ground assault capability, to launch an air 
operation against the bandit settlement called the Zhala camp. 
All intended targets have been destroyed. The planes completed 
their mission and returned to their base. 

</TEXT>

