<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Reiterates `Firm' Stance on FYROM Name </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Reiterates `Firm' Stance on FYROM Name </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1705173494 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1500 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1705173494 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today Government Spokesman Evangelos Venizelos said 
the Greek position on Skopje's [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia--FYROM] name has been stated and the Greek Government 
is not under any pressure. This was in reference to today's 
press reports and to UN mediator Cyrus Vance's meeting with 
Ambassador Khristos Zakharakis, the Foreign Ministry secretary 
general. He said the government is talking with everyone who 
has undertaken any initiative to resolve the issue and is 
seeking solutions. 
  Venizelos reiterated that Greece remains firm in its 
positions, and discussed the obvious U.S. interest toward a 
Skopje solution. 

</TEXT>

