<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Juppe Explains Bosnia Troop Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Juppe Explains Bosnia Troop Withdrawal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1705173694 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1600 
GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1705173694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Paris has threatened to take such a decision 
several times and Francois Leotard announced it this morning: 
France will withdraw 2,500 blue helmets from Bosnia; that is, a 
third of the French contingent, before the end of the year. 
[passage omitted] 
  The French Foreign Ministry adds a note of caution: this 
figure of 2,500 will have to be adjusted. First, because the 
withdrawal operation of 1,000 blue helmets from Sarajevo was 
already planned. As for the rest, we will wait and see, Alain 
Juppe says: 
  [Begin Juppe recording] This operation is under way. It is a 
gradual reduction, if I may say so, which was planned and 
announced within the context of the concentration of our troops 
in Sarajevo, an idea we have entertained for a long time. For 
the rest -- that is, the 1,500 men or so who are in Bihac -- 
their status will be considered by the end of the year but no 
final decision has yet been taken. This, I repeat, will depend 
on the development of the diplomatic process. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

