<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Sweden </F>
<H3> <TI>   Polish Foreign Minister Olechowski Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Polish Foreign Minister Olechowski Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1705174394 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1600 
GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1705174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] During a one-day visit to Sweden, Polish Foreign 
Minister Andrzej Olechowski had talks in Stockholm with Foreign 
Minister Margaretha af Ugglas. Minister Olechowski pointed out 
that Sweden, in entering the European Union [EU], will open the 
way to that organization for Poland and other Central and East 
European states. In his opinion, if Swedish society votes in 
the November referendum against Sweden's entry into the EU, this 
will probably make it impossible to start negotiations for other 
states to enter -- including Poland. 
  Margaretha af Ugglas stressed that her government was in 
favor of an open Europe and supported the Central and East 
European states' strivings to enter the EU. 

</TEXT>

