<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Reports on Emergency Region Operations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Reports on Emergency Region Operations </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    58 `Terrorists' Die in Southeast </H4>

<F P=102> TA1805111294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1805111294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over still of regional map] </F>
  [Text] Fifty-eight terrorists have been killed in 
operations launched by the security forces in the state of 
emergency region. Two terrorists have been captured in the 
operations. The State of Emergency Governor's Office has issued 
the following statement on the issue: 
  Operations aimed at preventing the activities of the 
militants belonging to the illegal separatist terror 
organization are continuing in the region at large. The 
security forces on 17 May launched an operation in the Bezar 
Mountain region, some 20 km north of Adiyaman, after learning 
that there was a large group of terrorists in that region. 
Twenty-eight terrorists were killed in the operation and their 
weapons were seized. 
  Meanwhile, other operations were also carried out by the 
security forces on 17 and 18 May. Seventeen terrorists were 
killed on the Kato Mountain west of Hakkari, four in the pursuit 
of terrorists who fired at buildings belonging to the security 
forces in central Siirt, three near the Ortabagi village of 
Sirnak's Uludere District, two around the Okcular village of 
Siirt's Pervari District, one in the Beybagi village of Batman's 
Kozluk District, one in the Kusluca village of Bitlis' Tatvan 
District, one in the Dallitepe region of Bingol, and one in the 
Akcay region of Sirnak's Cizre District. Rocket launchers and 
hand grenades were also seized. 
  Two terrorists were captured in the Ortabagi village of 
Sirnak's Uludere District and in central Van. 

</TEXT>

