<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Reports on Emergency Region Operations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Reports on Emergency Region Operations </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    15 `Terrorists,' 5 Security Members Die </H4>

<F P=102> TA1705185894 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1510 GMT 17 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1705185894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Diyarbakir, May 17 (A.A.) -- Fifteen terrorists and 
five security members were killed during clashes that broke out 
in the southeastern Provinces of Hakkari, Sirnak and Bingol, it 
was reported on Tuesday [17 May]. 
  A statement from the Regional Governor's Office said that 
six 
terrorists were killed in Caltepe, Hakkari, six in Gabar and 
Besta region of Sirnak, and three in Yedisu, Bingol. 
  Five members of security forces were killed by terrorists. 
The statement also said adding [word indistinct] long-range 
firearms and 22 hand grenades were also seized in these clashes. 
  In a series of security operations in Elazig center 17 
members of a terrorist organization were captured. Handguns, 
rockets and ammunition were seized in places shown by the 
terrorists. 
  It was also determined that they were responsible for the 
killing of 11 people, four attacks on official buildings, a bank 
robbery and logistic and financial support for the organization, 
the statement said, adding that 14 of them were later arrested. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

