<H3> <TI>   Ambassadors Receive Intelligence Briefing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ambassadors Receive Intelligence Briefing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1305155594 Istanbul SABAH in Turkish 4 May 94 p 13 </F>
<F P=103> NC1305155594 </F>
<F P=104>  Istanbul SABAH </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Intelligence Organization [NIO] held a 
briefing for 12 ambassadors and two permanent representatives 
yesterday. It has been learned that the Turkish ambassadors and 
permanent representatives, who have arrived to study the 
situation in southeastern Turkey, were briefed by NIO Under 
Secretary Sonmez Koksal for nearly four hours. The ambassadors 
then outlined the problems they have to deal with in Europe. 
  It has also been ascertained that the possibility of 
beginning a dialogue between the intelligence units and the 
ambassadors was discussed in the briefing. 

