<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Claims Greece Training Kurds </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Claims Greece Training Kurds </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1805152294 Athens ELEVTHEROTIPIA in Greek 18 May 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> NC1805152294 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ELEVTHEROTIPIA </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Istanbul--Turkish National Defense Minister Mehmet 
Golhan reiterated indirectly, but clearly, accusations that 
Greece trains Kurdish autonomists. Meeting with his Spanish 
counterpart, Golhan said Turkey has been fighting against PKK 
[Workers Party of Kurdistan] activities for the past 10 years. 
He also noted that this party causes damage in Europe by 
carrying out arms and narcotics trade, and said: "Germany and 
France have banned the activities of this organization." 
  The Turkish minister added: "We expect similar behavior from 
other countries. However, this is not done by certain 
neighbors, such as Greece. We have learned, through confessions 
by members of this organization, that certain people are trained 
in that country." 
  Referring to the Cyprus issue, he stressed that Turkey 
supports a solution that would appease both sides. 

</TEXT>

