<H3> <TI>   F-16 Production, Delivery to Egypt Under Way </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    F-16 Production, Delivery to Egypt Under Way </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1605165794 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1420 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1605165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, May 16 (A.A.) -- Turkey obtained important 
financial gains from the F-16 production for Egypt, the Defense 
Ministry said on Monday [16 May]. 
  A ministry secretary told the ANATOLIA Agency that according 
to the agreement signed previously between Egypt and the United 
States, two F-16 planes were manufactured and delivered to Egypt 
by Turkey on April 4. 
  According to the agreement, the planes were inspected by 
Tugas aviation and space industries. 
  The official said that there are no off-set agreements 
signed 
between Egypt and Turkey but that there is a memorandum of 
understanding on cooperation in defense industries between the 
two countries. 
  Turkey will deliver 44 more F-16's to Egypt on June 31, in 
line with the agreement. 

</TEXT>

