<H3> <TI>   First Quarter Import-Export Figures Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    First Quarter Import-Export Figures Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1405181694 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1508 GMT 14 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1405181694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, May 14 (A.A) -- Turkey's exports for the 
Jan-March 1994 period reached three billion 826 million 367 
thousand dollars while its imports totalled 5 billion 902 
million 128 thousand dollars for the same period, the State 
Statistics Institute (DIE) said on Saturday [14 May]. 
  According to DIE's written statement in March only, Turkey's 
exports were 1 billion 320 million 83 thousand dollars, while 
its imports were 1 billion 996 million 532 thousand dollars. 
  Exports in March increased by 7.2 percent compared to last 
year's 1 billion 231 million 149 thousand dollars for the same 
period. 
  As for imports, it decreased by 5.4 percent when compared to 
last years's 2 billion 110 million 911 thousand dollars. 
  During the Jan-March period exports increased by 4.2 percent 
compared to the same period last year, while imports decreased 
by 1.0 per thousand for the same period. 
  In the same period in 1993 exports were 3 billion 673 
million 
268 thousand dollars while for imports the amount was 5 billion 
908 million 27 thousand dollars. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

