<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] President Glavkos Kliridhis called on Great 
Britain, in its capacity as a permanent member of the UN 
Security Council, to play an active role in considering 
alternative ways to implement the UN resolutions on Cyprus. 
  Speaking at a ceremony for the presentation of the 
credentials of David Madden, the new British high commissioner 
in Cyprus, the president said the provocative defiance of these 
resolutions by the Turkish side is likely to hurt trust in the 
United Nations. President Kliridhis again attributed the lack 
of progress in the Cyprus issue to the lack of political will by 
the Turkish side. 
  Presenting his credentials, the new British high 
commissioner 
stressed that the division of Cyprus has lasted a long time and 
that the British Government desires to see Cyprus converted into 
a successful bicommunal and bizonal federation safe for all 
Cypriots. Madden said his priority will be a Cyprus settlement 
through negotiations between the Greek Cypriot and the Turkish 
Cypriot communities and welcomed the constructive approach 
maintained by the president toward realizing this goal. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

