<F P=102>   LD1805095694 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0917 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1805095694 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Hannover (DDP/ADN) -- Lower Saxony Interior 
Minister Gerhard Glogowski has announced a halt to the 
deportation of Kurds from his federal state to Turkey. Should 
the heads of the regional governments fail to decide tomorrow on 
a collective halt to deportation, Lower Saxony will act 
unilaterally, Glogowski told the Lower Saxony Landtag today. 
The interior minister assured the Landtag that at the moment no 
one is being sent from Lower Saxony to face death or torture. 
  In his speech, the text of which was released in advance, 
Glogowski stressed that no Kurds will be deported from Lower 
Saxony until the prime ministers' decision. The interior 
minister criticized the fact that weapons are again being 
supplied to Turkey, despite its being well-known that the 
Turkish Army uses them against the Kurds. The minister spoke of 
a war of extermination against the Kurds in Turkey. He called 
on Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel to take a firm stand to bring 
the murder in Turkey to an end. [passage omitted] 

