<H3> <TI>   Kohl Confident of Solving Problems in East </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohl Confident of Solving Problems in East </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1805101994 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0921 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1805101994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Heidelberg (DDP/ADN) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl said 
he is confident that the outstanding economic and social 
problems in eastern Germany can be resolved. The most important 
thing now is "to live in the spirit of common solidarity", Kohl 
said today at the opening of the new offices of a German 
research center in Heidelberg. Then one will have the strength, 
"to successfully get through the second great beginning for the 
second great stage of our republic." 
  The chancellor reiterated that spring brings with it a "new 
upswing in Germany." Order books are filling up again. Kohl 
pointed out that economic research institutes are expecting 
growth of 1.5 percent in Germany this year and show the carping 
critics that they are wrong. 
  The chancellor urged progress instead of stalling with 
regard 
to structural changes in the interest of Germany's future as a 
business and investment location. "A rethink instead of a 
redistribution" is necessary. 

</TEXT>

