<H3> <TI>   BKA Reports Organized Crime Increasing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    BKA Reports Organized Crime Increasing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1705130594 Munich FOCUS in German 16 May 94 p 11 </F>
<F P=103> AU1705130594 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich FOCUS </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "More and More Cover Firms"] </F>
  [Text] There is an alarming report by the Federal Office 
of Criminal Investigations [BKA]: "Organized crime has 
established itself in Germany." 
  From 1991 to 1993, trials involving organized crime doubled 
from 369 to 776; at the same time, the number of suspects rose 
from 5,149 to 9,884 -- with a proportion of foreigners of 54.5 
percent. In addition to drugs, the BKA registered increasing 
activities by gangs smuggling people but also concerning 
"illegal disposal of hazardous waste." 
  In 50 percent of the cases of organized crime, the gangs are 
nowadays conducting their business via German cover companies. 
The overall damage caused in 1993: almost 2 billion German 
marks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

