  [Excerpt] Madrid--Deputy Foreign Minister Yeoryios 
Papandreou was interviewed on Skopje [The Former Yugoslav 
Republic of Macedonia--FYROM] by the Spanish newspaper ABC. 
According to the MACEDONIAN NEWS AGENCY, Papandreou said that 
"he is not very sure of the outcome of the economic measures 
against Skopje," but added that there is new movement 
surrounding these negotiations. He expressed the hope that this 
could result in a solution to the problem. 
  According to the MACEDONIAN NEWS AGENCY, the deputy foreign 
minister expressed the hope "that a way to break the impasse of 
the talks will be found." He added: "For now, we are proposing 
a package of measures to strengthen mutual trust and to 
reexamine the name issue." Another point, Papandreou said, is 
that Greece is not afraid that it may be led to a military clash 
with Skopje. He stressed, however, that a clash with any side 
could cause war to spread. [passage omitted] 

