<H3> <TI>   Explosion Damages IBM Athens Office </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Explosion Damages IBM Athens Office </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1805060494 Paris AFP in English 2254 GMT 17 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1805060494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Athens, May 18 (AFP)--A blast wrecked the third 
floor offices of US computer giant IBM in a building in central 
Athens Tuesday evening [17 May], but no injuries were reported, 
police said. 
  A caller who said he was from the November 17 extremist 
group 
phoned a commercial radio station to give a warning a few 
minutes before the blast in the Sindagma building. 
  He said November 17 were going to fire a rocket at the 
building, although police could not immediately establish that a 
rocket had caused the blast. 
  Police cordoned off the entire area, which includes the 
Greek 
parliament and the new European parliament headquarters. 
  November 17 has assassinated more than 20 people and carried 
out around 50 bomb or rocket attacks since it surfaced in 1975 
with the murder of US Central Intelligence Agency (CIA) Athens 
station chief Richard Welch. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

