<H3> <TI>   Libyan Foreign Minister Visits in May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Libyan Foreign Minister Visits in May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1705202694 Paris TF-1 Television Network in French 1800 
GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1705202694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris TF-1 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Libyan foreign minister visited Paris twice 
during this current month. [passage omitted]. A report by 
Laurent Bazin, Eric Bourbotte, and David Cosset: 
  However official it might be, the visit smacks of heresy. 
Twice in less than a week, the Libyan foreign minister spent a 
few happy days in Paris, staying at the glamorous Hotel de 
Crillon. The first time [Libyan Foreign Minister] 'Umar 
al-Muntasir stopped in Paris was when he was on his way to South 
Africa. The second time, for a longer period, was on his return 
from South Africa. The long weekend was organized by his old 
friend, Adnan al-Khashoggi, a Saudi businessman who specializes 
in all kinds of transactions between the West and Arab 
countries. [passage omitted] 
  No official contact with al-Muntasir was made, the French 
Foreign Ministry stressed, but there was no reason to ban the 
visit: 
  [Begin Juppe recording] He is the foreign minister of a 
country with which France has not severed its diplomatic 
relations. When he asked us to travel via Paris, as was the 
case today, I don't see on what basis we could refuse the 
stopover. [end recording] 
  After a rest, the Libyan minister returned to Tripoli via 
Tunis. 

</TEXT>

