<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-096 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  17 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Disparages Veto </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Disparages Veto </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1705174894 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1430 GMT 
17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1705174894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "Senator Mancino has not accepted the clear verdict 
of the sovereign people, and he has not lost the habit of 
dreaming up new governmental alliances which, unlike those of 
the government of Silvio Berlusconi, belong to the partyocracy 
of the First Republic." 
  This was how Gianfranco Fini chose to comment on the veto 
made against Berlusconi by Mancino and by the Italian Popular 
Party [PPI], which had asked the prime minister to "modify the 
political picture" by dropping the National Alliance and forming 
a new ruling alliance with "the Democratic Alliance and the PPI." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

