<F P=101> Inter-European Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bonn To Ratify EU Treaties Before October Election </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bonn To Ratify EU Treaties Before October Election </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1605170294 Hamburg DPA in German 1308 GMT 16 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1605170294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Brussels (DPA) -- Germany plans to ratify the 
membership treaties of Austria, Sweden, Finland, and Norway with 
the European Union [EU] before the Bundestag elections in 
October. This was stated by Ursula Seiler-Albring, state 
minister in the Foreign Ministry in Bonn, in Brussels on Monday 
[16 May]. During a break in the meeting of the EU foreign 
ministers, the state minister stressed that Germany thus wants 
to make sure that the four new members will be accepted as of 1 
January 1995 in any case. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

