<H3> <TI>   CDU Condemns Magdeburg Riots </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CDU Condemns Magdeburg Riots </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1605153694 Hamburg DPA in German 1249 GMT 16 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1605153694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- The Federal Executive Committee of 
the Christian Democratic Union [CDU] has condemned the 
right-wing extremist riots in Magdeburg "with utmost severity." 
"Xenophobic excesses and all other acts of violence must be 
punished with the utmost severity of the law," CDU Secretary 
General Peter Hintze said in Bonn on Monday [16 May]. 
  The alleged violent criminals, who were arrested on 
Ascension 
Day [12 May], should not have been released again during the 
same night, Hintze stated. Saxony-Anhalt Minister-President 
Christoph Bergner (CDU) will investigate why the hooligans were 
released from police detention so quickly, he announced. 

</TEXT>

