<H3> <TI>   SPD Criticizes Police Behavior </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SPD Criticizes Police Behavior </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1605130794 Hamburg DPA in German 0936 GMT 16 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1605130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Halle -- The leadership of the Bundestag group of 
the Social Democratic Party of Germany [SPD] has sharply 
criticized the behavior of the police and judicial organs in 
connection with the bloody riots in Magdeburg last Thursday [12 
May]. SPD Deputy Chairman Wolfgang Thierse stated today at the 
end of a two-day visit to Saxony-Anhalt that it is unacceptable 
that the impression is being created that the perpetrators have 
been released again. This is an invitation for more acts of 
violence. The Magdeburg policy apparently did react resolutely 
enough. It is the state's duty to react to violence with all 
instruments that are available. 

</TEXT>

