<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Italy &amp; Vatican City </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Assures Western Allies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Assures Western Allies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1605125294 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1810 GMT 13 
May 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1605125294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Previti's Assurances on Defense </F>
Policy"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, May 13 -- Italy's new defense minister, 
Cesare Previti, the day after the government was sworn in, sent 
messages containing assurances to the secretaries of NATO and 
the WEU [Western European Union], as well as to the U.S. 
secretary of defense, to the effect that Italian policies of 
defense and security would keep to the firm traditional 
guidelines followed by previous Rome governments, the ministry 
information office reported this evening. 
  In his message, Previti said that Italy was firmly anchored 
to the Atlantic Alliance and deeply committed both to close 
relations with the United States and to the building of a 
credible European security identity. 
  The defense minister also emphasized the serious tensions 
that exist within an international framework and to which Italy, 
because of its geographical position, is particularly exposed. 

</TEXT>

