<H3> <TI>   PPI Denounces Berlusconi Government Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PPI Denounces Berlusconi Government Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1705104594 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 2145 GMT 16 
May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1705104594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Government Programme; Reactions, </F>
Italian People's Party"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, May 16 -- Senators from the Italian 
People's Party [PPI] (the former Christian Democrats) backed the 
document approved by the party leadership this evening which 
turned thumbs down on the speech Premier Silvio Berlusconi 
delivered to the Senate today prior to a confidence vote. 
  As a result, the PPI senators are expected to vote against 
the government which they accuse of showing no opening 
whatsoever to the opposition forces in parliament. 
  It was also learned that life senator Giulio Andreotti, a 
veteran Christian Democrat, discussed various scenarios with the 
PPI senators in the event the government does not win the 
confidence vote in the Senate. 
  In the document released by the party leadership this 
evening, the People's Party decried the government program put 
forth by Berlusconi as a mere list of promises with no 
indication as to how these generalized goals are to be achieved. 
  The PPI was especially sharp about the fact that Berlusconi 
in no way settled the problem of the conflict between his role 
as premier and his ownership of a large part of the means of 
communication in this country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

