<H3> <TI>   Poll Indicates Confidence in Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Indicates Confidence in Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1705093694 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1438 GMT 16 
May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1705093694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Two-Thirds of Italians Want </F>
Confidence Voted, Poll Says"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, May 16 -- Two-thirds of the Italian 
people want parliament to vote confidence in the Berlusconi 
government, a CIRM [Italian Center for Market Research] poll 
indicated. 
  66.4 percent of 911 persons polled in 180 towns around Italy 
replied Yes to the question "Would you vote confidence in the 
Berlusconi government if you were a member of the Lower House?" 
24.4 percent replied No and 9.2 percent expressed no view. 
  CIRM highlighted that one-third of Communist Refoundation 
voters and 0.4 percent of other Progressive voters would give 
the government their confidence, alongside a majority of Greens, 
the ex-Christian Democrats of the People's Party and the Pact 
for Italy, and the ex-radicals of the Pannella List. 

</TEXT>

