<H3> <TI>   Leotard: Troops To Withdraw if Embargo Lifted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Leotard: Troops To Withdraw if Embargo Lifted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1805193894 Paris TF-1 Television Network in French 1800 
GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1805193894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris TF-1 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Defense Minister Francois Leotard by Patrick </F>
Poivre d'Arvour, in Paris on 18 May -- live or recorded] 
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] [Poivre d'Arvor] Among the main 
proposals of Bernard-Henri Levy and his friends, there is the 
lifting of the arms embargo in favor of the Bosnian fighters who 
have been asking for it from the start. 
  [Leotard] This can be done, but the French troops would 
leave 
a quarter of an hour after that. We should know that supplying 
weapons would obviously mean extending the conflict. We cannot 
put in soldiers to act as a buffer force between the 
belligerents, and at the same time supply one of these 
belligerents with arms. It is clear that if weapons are 
supplied, in the quarter of an hour that follows, I would make 
the decision -- with the agreement of the prime minister and the 
president, of course -- to pull the French troops out. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

