  [Text] Denmark is saying no to a UN request to contribute 
personnel and equipment to the UN peacekeeping force in Rwanda. 
The Danish foreign minister says Denmark is already 
contributing UN troops at other sites. In addition, he 
questions whether the United Nations has a reasonable chance to 
carry out the task in Rwanda. 
  The United Nations has also asked Sweden to support the UN 
force in Rwanda. According to UN diplomats, Sweden could 
contribute engineering troops, helicopters, and hospitals. 

