<F P=104>  Helsinki HELSINGIN SANOMAT </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Unemployment in March at February </F>
Level"] 
  [Text] According to figures from the Government Office of 
Statistics, the number of unemployed in March remained at the 
level for February, but rose by more than 60,000 compared with 
March last year. The figure for seasonably adjusted unemployment 
also stabilized at the February level. 
  The jobless rate rose from March of last year to March of 
this year by 2.5 percent, or to 19.8 percent. The rate for males 
was a full 22 percent, while that for females was around 17 
percent. 
  There were around 100,000 unemployed youths. The rate for 
youth unemployment was 41 percent. 
  In the public sector and private service sector there were 
96,000 individuals without jobs, in industry 85,000, and in 
construction 74,000. The highest rate of unemployment was found 
in home construction, with nearly half of this sector's labor 
force not working. 

</TEXT>

