<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN's Feissel, Denktas Meet 18 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN's Feissel, Denktas Meet 18 May </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    U.S. Coordinator Disappointed </H4>

<F P=102> NC1905081294 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 0700 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1905081294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Robert Lamb, the U.S. State Department special 
coordinator on the Cyprus issue, expressed grave disappointment 
over Rauf Denktas' negative response to the 21 March document on 
the confidence-building measures. In a statement to CyBC [the 
Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation] in New York, the U.S. official 
said the current opportunity was the first in years to remove 
the deadlock and noted the need for a new direction. Lamb told 
the CyBC correspondent that Gustave Feissel has sent his report 
to UN Headquarters and that the Butrus-Ghali report to the 
Security Council would be submitted on Monday at the latest. 
  The U.S. official said he expects the bulk of the 
responsibility for the collapse of the talks to be attributed to 
Denktas. Asked what will follow the report, Lamb said it was 
too early to say and added that after the report is submitted 
there will be consultations among the Security Council members. 

</TEXT>

