<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   EP President Supports Cyprus EU Accession </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EP President Supports Cyprus EU Accession </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1905064494 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1905064494 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] European Parliament [EP] President Egon Klepsch has 
stated that the EP supports the European Union [EU] expansion 
through the accession of Cyprus and Malta, and that he will also 
support this position at the Corfu Summit conference to be held 
in June. Klepsch stressed: We must exert every effort toward 
finding a peaceful Cyprus solution. It would be an honor for 
whomever achieves this goal. 
  Klepsch, who is on a two-day official visit to Cyprus, made 
this statement after meeting with House of Representatives 
President Alexis Galanos this morning. 
  The House of Representatives president said Klepsch's visit 
stresses the EP decision and collective desire to support 
Cyprus' efforts for its accession to the EU. Galanos noted: The 
most substantive message to the Turkish side so that it may sit 
at the talks with the political will to find a solution is for 
the talks on Cyprus' accession to the EU to begin in January 
1995. Galanos said he was satisfied with Klepsch's moral support 
in these difficult times. 
  The EP president also met with party leaders and 
representatives today. Now he is in a meeting with President 
Glavkos Kliridhis. 

</TEXT>

