<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ataman To Resettle Citizens From Iraq </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ataman To Resettle Citizens From Iraq </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1905061994 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
2000 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1905061994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Turkey has announced that if the citizens who went 
to northern Iraq because they were forced into it at gunpoint or 
intimidated into doing it by the terrorist organization want to 
come back, the necessary steps will be taken to resettle them 
safely. 
  Replying to a question during his weekly news conference, 
Foreign Ministry spokesman Ataman said that the citizens who 
went to northern Iraq in this way should see that they were 
tricked. A terrorist organization can promise nothing but blood 
and tears, he stressed, adding: Consequently, if they decide to 
return to their country, we will naturally open our arms to 
these citizens. There is no doubt that our state will do 
whatever it can to resettle these people and ensure their 
welfare. 

</TEXT>

