<H3> <TI>   Returns, Notes Developing Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Returns, Notes Developing Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1905111494 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1010 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1905111494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, May 18 (A.A) -- Parliament Speaker 
Husamettin Cindoruk who was in Georgia to attend the Black Sea 
Economic Cooperation Parliamentary Assembly (KEIPA) returned to 
Ankara on Wednesday [18 May] after concluding talks. 
  He told reporters at Ankara's Esenboga Airport that he held 
positive talks with Georgian Head of State Eduard Shevardnadze 
and other senior officials. 
  "KEIPA has started to reach results. Specially in the 
Azeri-Armenian conflict, we hope our propositions will help in 
its solution," he said. 
  He added they were very well received by Shevardnadze and 
present bilateral relations are steadily developing. 

</TEXT>

