<H3> <TI>   Ankara Plans Contribution to CSCE in Caucasus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ankara Plans Contribution to CSCE in Caucasus </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1805135194 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1805135194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] It has been announced that Turkey is ready to make 
every possible contribution of observers to the Caucasus within 
the framework of the CSCE and to meeting the personnel and other 
requirements of this mission. 
  Foreign Ministry spokesman Ferhat Ataman, replying to a 
question at his weekly news conference, stressed that Turkey, as 
a responsible member of the international community, actively 
participates in efforts to secure world peace and stability. 
Recalling that Turkey contributed to the UN peacekeeping forces 
in Somali and Bosnia-Herzegovina, Ataman added that Turkey is 
willing to fulfill its other international responsibilities with 
the same conscientious attitude. 
  [Begin Ataman recording] As a matter of fact, Turkey is 
ready to make every possible contribution of observers to the 
Caucasus within the framework of the CSCE and to meeting the 
personnel and other requirements of this mission in order to 
solve the dispute between Azerbaijan and Armenia peacefully 
through the Armenian withdrawal from Azerbaijani territory and 
in order to establish an atmosphere of stability in the 
Caucasus. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

