<H3> <TI>   Ankara Security Director Reinstated After Inquiry </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ankara Security Director Reinstated After Inquiry </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1905093494 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1558 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1905093494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, May 18 (A.A.) -- Orhan Tasanlar was 
reinstated as Ankara security director today, after being 
removed following the roughing up of May Day celebrators and a 
deputy by the police on May 1. 
  After assuming his post in the morning, Tasanlar told the 
Anatolian Agency that Turkey was a state of law and everything 
took place before the public. 
  `The inspectors concluded their interrogation and could not 
find any element of crime against me,' he said. `There, the 
state was destroyed. What I regretted most was the fact that 
the police were injured and state vehicles were destroyed in the 
incidents which broke out on May Day and no one mentioned this.' 
  Interior Minister Nahit Mentese had removed Tasanlar from 
his 
position temporarily after calls from the government's junior 
coalition partner Social Democratic Populist Party (SHP) for an 
investigation into the charges of police brutality. 

</TEXT>

