<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Balladur Comments On Troops in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Balladur Comments On Troops in Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1805165194 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1600 
GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1805165194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bosnia: Edouard Balladur has announced the partial 
withdrawal of the peacekeeping troops from former Yugoslavia. 
The withdrawal from Bihac will take place in six months. As 
for the destination of this contingent, France will decide on 
what action to take, depending on the progress of the peace 
process. Edouard Balladur was speaking in the National Assembly: 
  [Begin Balladur recording] Things are clear, ladies and 
gentlemen, we are at the service of the United Nations and at 
the service of a policy aimed at restoring peace. If this 
restoration of peace were to prove impossible, if the other 
powers were not working toward this end, then, as I said last 
week, we should be forced to ask ourselves questions about the 
meaning and duration of our action. We do not have to blush; 
quite the contrary, we can be proud of what we have done, and of 
what we are continuing to do. We have the largest number of 
soldiers -- by a long way -- at the service of peace on the 
territory of former Yugoslavia. We are quite prepared to 
continue with our efforts, on condition that every party is 
willing to make its own contribution. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

