<F P=100> PORTUGAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Names New Agriculture Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Names New Agriculture Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1805182994 Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network in Portuguese 
1600 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1805182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] There has been a government reshuffle: Prime 
Minister Cavaco Silva has replaced Agriculture Minister Arlindo 
Cunha with Antonio Duarte Silva. The ministry's existing 
secretaries of state will remain in office. Antonio Duarte 
Silva is practically unknown, apart from the fact that he was 
included in the Social Democratic Party list of candidates for 
the European Parliament. More details from Pedro Cid: 
  [Cid] We know very little about the new minister, he is 
unknown to public opinion, but he has some kind of professional 
political background. He was a secretary of state once at the 
same ministry and his most recent job was that of president of 
the Viana do Castelo shipyard. [passage omitted] 
  He is a mechanical engineer and was once taught at Lisbon's 
Instituto Superior Tecnico. 

</TEXT>

