  The Greek side insists on all questions and decisions being 
raised before the meeting, which is anticipated to be held 
before the end of July, so the two ministers will be in a 
position to "close" the differences. 
  According to the Greek proposal, these meetings could be 
held 
at the border-crossing of Kakavia, alternatively on Greek and 
Albanian territory. 

