<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ahtisaari Visits Russia, Discusses Trade Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ahtisaari Visits Russia, Discusses Trade Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905211394 Helsinki Suomen Yleis Radio Network in Finnish 
1430 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1905211394 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleis Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Finnish President Martti Ahtisaari is very 
pleased with his visit to Russia, which ended today. [passage 
omitted] 
  President Martti Ahtisaari, unlike previous presidents, 
carried out his first official visit to Russia according to a 
short schedule. During his visit, which only lasted 25 hours, 
Ahtisaari had time to meet President Boris Yeltsin and Premier 
Viktor Chernomyrdin several times. This morning he met the 
leaders of both chambers of Parliament. On returning to 
Finland, Ahtisaari reiterated that there are no political 
problems between the two countries. 
  According to the president, future relations will be handled 
more and more between the parliaments. He cited as an example 
the exchange of visits by the Foreign Affairs Committees. 
[passage omitted] 
  According to the president, when Finland becomes a member of 
the European Union [EU], trade between Finland and Russia will 
be guided primarily by agreements between Russia and the EU. 
  The industrial delegation that accompanied Ahtisaari on his 
visit held talks with the Russians that concentrated on how the 
financing of individual deals could be guaranteed. There is 
currently no comprehensive system in Russia which would 
guarantee repayment of loans. No individual large deals were 
signed during the trip. 
  At the end of the presidential news conference given at 
Helsinki-Vantaa Airport, the president explained when asked what 
he did late last night. According to Ahtisaari, the atmosphere 
at the dinner was enlivened mainly by good orchestral music. 
After the dinner, which ended at about 2100, he had discussions 
with the Finnish industrial delegation. The president's night 
ended with a football match between AC Milan and Barcelona. 
[passage omitted] [end recording] 

</TEXT>

