<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Spokesman Urges Alternative UN Solutions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Spokesman Urges Alternative UN Solutions </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Greece Supports Cyprus </H4>

<F P=102> NC1905180494 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1600 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1905180494 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Greek Government has expressed the conviction 
that following the latest developments, the Cyprus issue has 
reached the point where the UN secretary general should assess 
the situation, determine who is responsible for it, and present 
a report to the Security Council. Greek Foreign Ministry 
Spokesman Konstandinos Bikas said alternative solutions to the 
Cyprus issue should also be examined, adding that it is not 
possible to continue the current time consuming process. This, 
he said, is necessary because of the continuing Turkish 
intransigence and the lack of political will, which were 
confirmed at the latest meeting between Gustave Feissel, the UN 
secretary general's deputy special representative in Cyprus, and 
[Turkish Cypriot Leader Rauf] Denktas. 

</TEXT>

