<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Europeans Support EU Membership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Shows Europeans Support EU Membership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1905191494 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1600 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1905191494 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The majority of the peoples in the European Union 
[EU] support a quick accession of Cyprus to the Union. A poll 
conducted for the EU last February and made public today shows 
that 53 percent of the Europeans in the poll support the quick 
accession of Cyprus, 35 percent were against, and 12 percent did 
not express an opinion. 
  Regarding Turkey, the poll had a negative result: 43 percent 
of those asked were in favor of Turkey's accession and 48 
percent were against. Of those in favor of Cyprus' accession, 
first were the Greeks, then the Irish, followed by the Spaniards 
and British. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

