<H3> <TI>   Garcia Vargas Seeks Reduction of Bosnia Contingent </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Garcia Vargas Seeks Reduction of Bosnia Contingent </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905140094 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1300 GMT 19 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1905140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE International </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister Julian Garcia Vargas has announced 
that he wants to achieve a gradual reduction of the Spanish blue 
helmet contingent in Bosnia. In addition, Garcia Vargas said the 
soldiers are to be replaced by aid workers and Spanish 
businessmen who will help to rebuild Mostar. Julian Garcia 
Vargas. 
  [Begin Garcia Vargas recording] In our case, if the 
pacification of Mostar goes ahead as planned, it is probable 
that in the next few months I will think about a reduction, 
mainly because the blue helmets will be replaced by civilian 
experts, aid workers, and businessmen [end recording] 

</TEXT>

