<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Spokesman Urges Alternative UN Solutions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Spokesman Urges Alternative UN Solutions </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Denktas Avoiding Responsibility </H4>

<F P=102> NC1905125494 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1905125494 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis has said 
that Rauf Denktas' ongoing statements about progress in the 
confidence-building measures are part of his tactics to avoid 
being accused of responsibility for the deadlock by the UN 
secretary general's report. Kasoulidhis added: On the basis of 
the official briefing by Gustave Feissel, no progress was made 
in Vienna. The spokesman made it clear that the Cypriot 
Government does not want to discuss with the United Nations or 
anybody else anything beyond the 21 March document, which the 
Cypriot side has accepted as it stands. Kasoulidhis noted: Any 
talk with us is out of context, since the negotiations are being 
held with the other side. 
  Answering a question, the government spokesman said there is 
no information about the United Nations having amended the 21 
March document, and added that the time limits the Security 
Council set for discussing the confidence-building measures have 
expired. Kasoulidhis stressed: What is expected following the 
UN secretary general's report is to determine alternative ways 
of promoting the UN resolutions. Our side will cooperate only 
through this process. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

