<F P=106> [Unattributed article from Brussels EUROPE: "Results of </F>
Ecofin Council Session"] 
  [Text] Meeting on Monday [16 May] at a session chaired by 
Giorgos Romeos, Greek Deputy Minister for the National Economy, 
the Ecofin [economic and financial issues] Council concluded its 
work shortly after 1800. Its results were summarized as 
follows: 

  -  Economic situation. The Council took note of the 
Commission's new projections, which were nevertheless sharply 
criticized by Chancellor of the Exchequer Kenneth Clarke as 
regards the United Kingdom. Belgian Minister Philippe Maystadt 
said the Commission had made low-range projections for certain 
Member States. 
  -  Progress of work on the white paper. Based on a 
Commission note, the Twelve continued preparation of the Corfu 
Summit, examining in particular a German memorandum which was 
warmly endorsed by the British delegation. 
  -  Financial assistance 
to Central and East European countries. The expected decisions 
were taken in part. 
  -  Combatting fraud. The ministers held the 
expected exchange of views. 
  -  Banks. The Council adopted the 
directive on the guarantee system. 
  -  Securities exchanges. The 
Council completed and simplified the directive on prospectuses 
for admission of shares to the exchange. 


</TEXT>

