<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Foreign Ministry spokesman Radko Vlaykov] </F>
  [Text] London, May 19 -- Bulgarian Foreign Minister 
Stanislav Daskalov started his working visit to Britain today. 
  Foreign Minister Daskalov's visit is a continuation of 
Bulgaria's efforts to maintain regular dialogue with the EU 
[European Union] member states. 
  The most important of Mr. Daskalov's meetings here was his 
working lunch and meeting with British Foreign Secretary Douglas 
Hurd and with other senior Foreign Office representatives. The 
two sides discussed a wide range of issues of mutual interest 
and Balkan security issues. They exchanged opinions on the 
situation in the former Yugoslavia and in Bosnia-Herzegovina in 
particular. The Bulgarian foreign minister recalled Bulgaria's 
stand against Balkan countries' participation in the UNPROFOR 
[UN Protection Forces] in Bosnia-Herzegovina. The two sides 
also discussed issues of bilateral relations. 
  Foreign Minister Stanislav Daskalov also visited the British 
Parliament where he met Michael Marshall, chairman of the 
Interparliamentary Group and chairman of the Group for 
British-Bulgarian Parliamentary Cooperation. 

</TEXT>

