<H3> <TI>   Ruehe Urges `Special Role' for Russia in NATO </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ruehe Urges `Special Role' for Russia in NATO </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1905171594 Hamburg DPA in German 1531 GMT 19 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1905171594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Oxford (DPA) -- According to Defense Minister Volker 
Ruehe, Russia is entitled to play a certain special role in 
security partnership with NATO, but it should not make 
exaggerated demands. In a speech at St. Antony's College of 
Oxford University on 19 May, Ruehe said according to the draft 
text that Russia should not be treated like Tajikistan or 
Albania. "However, it must learn to see itself as Russia, as 
neighbor among neighbors, and as a partner among basically 
equals, and act accordingly." He said it was understandable 
that Russia as a big power wanted to play a part in pan-European 
security issues. Moscow should become a strategic partner of 
NATO, but "must not hinder our neighbors' step-by-step 
integration into Western structures." 

</TEXT>

