<H3> <TI>   Bonn To Build Homes for Ethnic Germans in Siberia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bonn To Build Homes for Ethnic Germans in Siberia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1905104994 Hamburg DPA in German 0920 GMT 19 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1905104994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn -- The government wants to build 2,000 
apartments for ethnic Germans in western Siberia before the end 
of the year. This was announced by the government's 
representative for resettlers, State Secretary Horst 
Waffenschmidt (Christian Democratic Union), in Bonn today. 
  The apartments are designed for ethnic Germans who do not 
want to emigrate to Germany, but who are looking for new homes 
because of the unstable situation in their home country, 
particularly in Kazakhstan. The government wants to provide 30 
million German marks for these measures and buy houses, build 
new homes, or grant credits for self-help measures. At present, 
about 600,000 ethnic Germans are living in western Siberia. 

</TEXT>

