<F P=103> AU2005102694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Magdeburg -- According to the public prosecutor, 
the attack by right-wing radicals on the Marietta bar in 
Magdeburg on 12 May was planned. The personnel received a 
corresponding hint before 12 May but did not inform the police, 
Saxony-Anhalt Senior Public Prosecutor Juergen Hossfeld told 
journalists in Magdeburg today. Five black Africans fled to the 
bar after being brutally beaten and chased through the streets 
by about 60 right-wing radicals. 
  One day before the riots, the Federal Office for the 
Protection of the Constitution warned the police against attacks 
by right-wing extremists. Interior and Justice Minister Walter 
Remmers (Christian Democratic Union) stressed that there was no 
reason to assume that the suspicions of the Federal Office for 
the Protection of the Constitution would come true. 

