<F P=103> AU2005192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Magdeburg (DPA) -- Saxony-Anhalt Free Democratic 
Party [FDP] chairman Peter Kunert has called upon his party's 
representatives to vote for the Johannes Rau, the Social 
Democratic Party's [SPD] candidate, in the presidential election 
in Berlin on 23 May. In a statement published in Magdeburg on 
20 May, he says that it would be a wrong signal to vote for a 
conservative like Roman Herzog, the candidate of the Christian 
Democratic Union/Christian Social Union. 
  Kunert does not assume that his own party's candidate, 
Hildegard Hamm-Bruecher, will get a majority of the Federal 
Convention. He argues that, unlike Herzog, Rau has the 
capability of integrating people and building bridges beyond 
ideological differences. Kunert says that the social democrat 
could be the federal president of all Germans, beyond party 
borders. 

