<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Hamburg (DPA) -- The Federal Executive Committee 
has removed its own chairman, Bernd Schuenemann, from office and 
simultaneously initiated proceedings on his expulsion from the 
party. The majority in the executive committee accuses the 
Munich lawyer of having violated the statutes, resolutions of 
the Federal Executive Committee, and principles of the party. 
  "On his own authority," Schuenemann pursued the founding of 
an Instead Party in Saarland and did not check the infiltration 
